"43949.551388888889"	"43949.556944444441"	"100"	"455"	"1"	"43949.556944444441"	"R_2dKlvEfROoV9m8r"	"anonymous"	"EN"	"I consent"	"8640 C"	"Yes"	">1 year"	"5 or more"	">40"	"Urban Metro area >300,000 (e.g. Cleveland-Akron, Columbus, Cincinnati)"	""	"Low"	""	"Specialty Surgery (please specify)"	"Urology, also worked primarily as ER scribe but cannot select two"	""	""	"Other (please describe)"	"Emergency Services Inc, Central Ohio Urology"	"Other (Please describe, include smaller hospitals of UH/CCF/MetroHealth, e.g. UH Pharma)"	"Mount Carmel health system"	"Unsure (please specify)"	"It may have, not entirely sure since it took 3 cycles to get in"	""	"Extremely helpful"	"Placing diseases into the context of an already-developed framework is much easier than learning all of it anew. I would say I am one of the top performers in my class because of it."	"Extremely helpful"	"Can recall many procedures and practices in the ER, lots of little clinical tidbits picked up over the course of 2 years as a scribe"	"Extremely helpful"	""
