"43949.589583333334"	"43949.597916666666"	"100"	"698"	"1"	"43949.597916666666"	"R_27TL70wLamCLxOJ"	"anonymous"	"EN"	"I consent"	"8764R"	"Yes"	"7-12 months"	"45720"	"21-30"	"Inner Ring Suburban >10,000 (e.g. Cleveland: Lakewood, Cleveland Heights, Euclid; Columbus: Merion Village, Eastmoor)"	""	"Low"	""	"Emergency"	""	""	""	"Other (please describe)"	"PhysAssist which I think is now owned by another scribe company. "	"Other (Please describe, include smaller hospitals of UH/CCF/MetroHealth, e.g. UH Pharma)"	"Dayton Children's Hospital "	"Unsure (please specify)"	"I would believe it did since it gave me a lot of experience with physicians and patients, but I am not 100% sure. "	""	"Extremely helpful"	"I came into medical school knowing the language and I think it has helped me when learning about diseases being able to connect them back to the experiences I had and the patients I saw while scribing. "	"Very helpful"	"If \"N/A, no clinical experience including CCE\" means not having a CCE then since I have had them I would say it has helped with with knowing how to structure a patient interview. "	"Extremely helpful"	"I think scribing is a wonderful opportunity. I was paid at the low end of what scribes make, so I wish that would have been better to help me through college especially given the hours I would work. However, I would do it again and every time I talk with a premedical student I suggest scribing as a way to get experience. "
